<div class="block">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="block__content">
      <p>Street Support Network is a central online resource around homelessness in a city, currently available in Greater Manchester, Leeds, Bradford, Bournemouth, Portsmouth & Liverpool, with other cities keen to join.</p>
      <p>We have a simple mission - to make it easier for people who are homeless to get the help they need...</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/find-help/">Find Help</a>: Find local services based on need - see exactly when and where help is available, and where there are gaps.</li>
        <li><a href="/give-help/">Give Help</a>: Find out what you can do to help - see what is needed across all organisations, volunteer, offer items, or donate.</li>
        <li><a href="http://news.streetsupport.net/">News</a>: Learn about homelessness in the city - stories, information, and updates on what is being done to improve things.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We make it easier for the local network of services to collaborate, co-ordinate and provide better support for people experiencing homelessness, and we make it easier for citizens and businesses to DO something to help. Many small, co-ordinated actions add up to a big difference to homeless people in the city.</p>
      <p>Our long term vision is a place-driven citizen-led support network, with people with personal lived experience of homelessness at the centre.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

